The paper deals with the analysis of probabilistic programs, which involves techniques from logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of concentration inequalities and moments also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control theory/systems (cs.SY).
